body:
Title says it all; the solidity code (and its conversion to abi) state that a `uint32[2][3]` is returned, but the generated go-binding only returns the inner array: `[2]uint32`.

#### System information

```
$ geth version
Version: 1.7.3-stable
Git Commit: 4bb3c89d44e372e6a9ab85a8be0c9345265c763a
Architecture: amd64
Protocol Versions: [63 62]
Network Id: 1
Go Version: go1.9.2
Operating System: linux
```

#### Expected behaviour
`GetTarget` binding should return `([3][2]uint32, error)`, i.e. a nested array, like the ABI and the solidity code declare.

#### Actual behaviour
It generates the go-bindings, but with this snippet, which seems incorrect to me:
```go
// GetTarget is a free data retrieval call binding the contract method 0x89d6d989.
//
// Solidity: function GetTarget() constant returns(uint32[2][3])
func (_BugTest *BugTestCaller) GetTarget(opts *bind.CallOpts) ([2]uint32, error) {
	var (
		ret0 = new([2]uint32)
	)
	out := ret0
	err := _BugTest.contract.Call(opts, out, "GetTarget")
	return *ret0, err
}
```

#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour


1) Create file `BugTest.sol`:
```soldity
pragma solidity ^0.4.19;
pragma experimental ABIEncoderV2;

contract BugTest {

    uint constant InnerSize = 2;
    uint constant OuterSize = 3;

    function GetTarget() public pure returns (uint32[InnerSize][OuterSize]) {
        uint32[InnerSize][OuterSize] memory result;
        // Imagine more advanced usage of the nested array ...
        result[0][0] = 1;
        result[0][1] = 2;
        result[1][0] = 3;
        result[1][1] = 4;
        result[2][0] = 5;
        result[2][1] = 6;
        return result;
    }
}
```
2.1) Create abi: run `solc -o build --abi --overwrite BugTest.sol`
2.2) Or use the abi it generated for me:
```json
[{"constant":true,"inputs":[],"name":"GetTarget","outputs":[{"name":"","type":"uint32[2][3]"}],"payable":false,"stateMutability":"pure","type":"function"}]
```

3) Create the go-binding, using the generated abi: `abigen --abi build/BugTest.abi --pkg abi --type BugTest --out "bug_test_binding.go"`
4) Check generated go bindings.
